4.get input for 3 variables,name,score and department.let the user enter the score for 100marks you convert it for 10 and print it.
Source code:
import java.util.Scanner;
class Namebasedproblem
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Enter name");
        String a = sc.nextLine();
        System.out.println("Enter score");
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        sc.nextLine();
        System.out.println("Enter department");
        String c = sc.nextLine();
        System.out.println("Name: " + a);
        System.out.println("Score: " + b);
        double scores = b / 10.0;
        System.out.println("Score by 10: " + scores);
        System.out.println("Department: " + c);

        sc.close();
    }
}
=======================================================
5.Write a Java program to divide two numbers and print them on the screen.
Source code:
import java.util.Scanner;

class Hello {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        System.out.println("Enter a");
        int a = sc.nextInt();

        System.out.println("Enter b");
        int b = sc.nextInt();

        // Check if b is not zero
        if (b != 0) {
            int c = a / b;
            System.out.println("The result is " + c);
        } else {
            System.out.println("Error: Division by zero is not allowed.");
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}
=============================================
